---
description: Core architecture constraints for all generation tasks (English logic, Chinese output)
globs: src/**/*.{ts,vue,tsx}
alwaysApply: true
---

<rule>
  <context>
    You act as a Senior Frontend Architect for this Vue 3 custom stack (Vite, Vue 3.5+, TypeScript, UnoCSS, PrimeVue, Alova, Pinia).
    This rule defines the global architecture, tooling, and router constraints for all code generation tasks.
  </context>

  <workflow>
    <step>Before generating any code, always read and follow <file>docs/ai-specs/PROJECT_PROTOCOL.md</file>.</step>
    <step>If a task involves programmatic rendering (for example dialog contentRenderer), read <file>docs/ai-specs/AI_CODING_PROTOCOL.md</file> and follow its decision flow; ensure <code>lang="tsx"</code> when using JSX in <code>.vue</code>.</step>
    <step>When architecture or directory responsibilities are unclear, read <file>docs/architecture/ARCHITECTURE_OVERVIEW.md</file> and <file>docs/architecture/DIRECTORY_STRUCTURE.md</file> before writing code.</step>
    <step>When adding logic, store, component, or API code, first inspect the golden samples in <file>docs/ai-specs/GOLDEN_SAMPLES/</file> and strictly match their style.</step>
    <step>When generating PrimeVue code, read <file>docs/ai-specs/PRIMEVUE_V4_API.md</file> and always use v4 component names (for example <code>Select</code>, <code>DatePicker</code>, <code>Drawer</code>); never use deprecated v3 names such as <code>Dropdown</code>, <code>Calendar</code>, <code>InputSwitch</code>, or <code>Sidebar</code>.</step>
  </workflow>

  <constraints>
    <section name="package-manager">
      <rule>Use <code>pnpm</code> as the default package manager for install/dev/build/lint commands; fall back to <code>npm</code> only if pnpm is unavailable.</rule>
      <rule>When showing commands or documentation, prefer <code>pnpm install</code>, <code>pnpm dev</code>, etc., and do not default to <code>npm run</code> unless explicitly requested.</rule>
    </section>

    <section name="architecture-negative-constraints">
      <rule>Use the Composition API with <code>&lt;script setup lang="ts"&gt;</code> only; never use the Options API.</rule>
      <rule>Never call <code>axios</code> or <code>fetch</code> directly in business code; always use the project Alova instance via <file>@/utils/http</file> or <file>@/hooks/modules/useHttpRequest</file>.</rule>
      <rule>Do not write raw CSS for layout, spacing, or colors in <code>&lt;style&gt;</code> blocks; use UnoCSS utility classes and semantic design tokens instead.</rule>
      <rule>Do not hardcode pixel/rem values or hex colors; use semantic classes from <file>uno.config.ts</file> or CSS variables such as <code>rgb(var(--primary))</code>.</rule>
      <rule>Do not use inline styles such as <code>style="padding: 16px"</code>; always express layout via UnoCSS classes.</rule>
      <rule>Do not use TypeScript syntax (type annotations, assertions, generics) inside Vue templates; move all typing into <code>&lt;script setup&gt;</code>.</rule>
      <rule>Do not rely on implicit type inference for business variables; always declare explicit types.</rule>
      <rule>In business logic (views, components, composables, stores), do not use <code>any</code>; define strict interfaces in <file>src/types/</file> or colocated with the file.</rule>
      <rule>Allow <code>any</code> only inside a small, documented boundary layer whitelist:
        <list>
          <item><file>src/hooks/modules/useHttpRequest.ts</file> (Alova generic glue)</item>
          <item><file>src/utils/lodashes.ts</file> (lodash-es wrapper)</item>
          <item><file>src/utils/safeStorage/**</file> (encryption / storage adapters)</item>
          <item><file>src/utils/date/**</file> (date adapters)</item>
          <item><file>src/components/UseEcharts/**</file> (ECharts option/event boundary)</item>
          <item><file>src/hooks/modules/useChartTheme/**</file> (chart theme boundary)</item>
        </list>
      </rule>
      <rule>When using <code>any</code> in these boundary files, keep it scoped to the smallest internal detail and add a short comment describing the expected shape.</rule>
    </section>

    <section name="design-system">
      <rule>Before generating UI code, always align with the theme system:
        <list>
          <item>Types: <file>src/types/systems/theme.d.ts</file></item>
          <item>Constants: <file>src/constants/theme.ts</file></item>
          <item>Store: <file>src/stores/modules/theme.ts</file></item>
          <item>Use semantic color tokens such as <code>text-primary</code>, <code>bg-surface-ground</code>, <code>text-info</code> instead of hex values.</item>
        </list>
      </rule>
      <rule>Respect the size system:
        <list>
          <item>Types: <file>src/types/systems/size.d.ts</file></item>
          <item>Constants: <file>src/constants/size.ts</file>, <file>src/constants/sizeScale.ts</file></item>
          <item>Store: <file>src/stores/modules/size.ts</file></item>
          <item>Use semantic size classes such as <code>px-padding-lg</code>, <code>fs-md</code>; do not hardcode pixel values.</item>
        </list>
      </rule>
      <rule>Respect the layout and responsive system:
        <list>
          <item>Use <file>src/constants/breakpoints.ts</file> and <file>src/constants/layout.ts</file> as the single source of truth.</item>
          <item>Use <file>src/stores/modules/device.ts</file> and <file>src/stores/modules/layout.ts</file> for breakpoint and layout state.</item>
          <item>Follow <file>docs/ai-specs/ADAPTIVE_LAYOUT.md</file> when dealing with layout shell, sidebar visibility, or orientation.</item>
        </list>
      </rule>
      <rule>Use UnoCSS classes defined in <file>uno.config.ts</file> and avoid adding ad-hoc CSS for things that can be expressed via existing semantic utilities.</rule>
    </section>

    <section name="behavior">
      <rule>Separate business logic and UI: put feature logic in composables under <file>src/hooks/</file>, UI-only components in <file>src/components/</file>, and container pages in <file>src/views/</file>.</rule>
      <rule>For dialogs, modals, feedback prompts, and confirmation flows, use <code>useDialog()</code> from <file>@/hooks/modules/useDialog</file> and follow <file>docs/ai-specs/DIALOG_COMPONENT.md</file>; do not create ad-hoc dialog implementations.</rule>
      <rule>For lightweight notifications outside component context (for example HTTP interceptors, global error handlers), use <code>window.$toast</code> and <code>window.$message</code> as documented in <file>docs/ai-specs/TOAST_AND_MESSAGE.md</file>; do not build custom global notification systems.</rule>
      <rule>Do not manually import Vue runtime APIs such as <code>ref</code>, <code>computed</code>, <code>watch</code>; rely on the build system auto-import configuration in <file>docs/ai-specs/BUILD_SYSTEM.md</file> and remove unused imports, prefixing intentionally unused variables with <code>_</code>.</rule>
      <rule>After generating code, self-check against the relevant golden sample in <file>docs/ai-specs/GOLDEN_SAMPLES/</file> and adjust style to match.</rule>
    </section>

    <section name="router-system">
      <rule>Treat the router system as a first-class architecture component whenever routes, menus, breadcrumbs, permission guards, or dynamic routes are involved.</rule>
      <rule>For login, logout, token handling, or HTTP 401 behavior, follow <file>docs/ai-specs/AUTH_AND_LOGIN_FLOW.md</file> before changing any code.</rule>
      <rule>When modifying routes:
        <list>
          <item>Read the router section in <file>docs/ai-specs/PROJECT_PROTOCOL.md</file> and <file>src/types/modules/router.d.ts</file> (<code>RouteMeta</code>, <code>RouteConfig</code>, <code>BackendRouteConfig</code>, <code>RouteModule</code>, <code>RouteUtils</code>, <code>DynamicRouteManager</code>).</item>
          <item>Define all static routes only under <file>src/router/modules/*.ts</file> using <code>RouteConfig | RouteConfig[]</code>; never define static routes directly in <code>router/index.ts</code> or in views/components.</item>
          <item>Always set complete <code>meta</code> information (title, parent, rank, roles/auths, keepAlive, tag flags, external link data, etc.).</item>
        </list>
      </rule>
      <rule>For backend-provided routes, always use <code>BackendRouteConfig</code> and convert them via <code>processAsyncRoutes</code> in <file>src/router/utils/common.ts</file>; do not manually map async routes in arbitrary modules.</rule>
      <rule>When computing menus, breadcrumbs, flat routes, or keepAlive lists, always use <code>routeUtils</code> from <file>src/router/index.ts</file> and helpers from <file>src/router/utils/common.ts</file> instead of reimplementing them.</rule>
      <rule>Register global <code>beforeEach</code>/<code>afterEach</code> guards only inside <file>src/router/utils/guards.ts</file> via <code>usePermissionGuard</code> and <code>registerRouterGuards</code>; never add global guards from views, components, or hooks.</rule>
      <rule>Manage dynamic routes only through <code>DynamicRouteManager</code> created by <code>createDynamicRouteManager(router)</code>; do not call <code>router.addRoute</code> or <code>router.removeRoute</code> directly.</rule>
      <rule>For navigation, back, refresh, and new-window behaviors, use helper functions from <file>src/router/utils/helper.ts</file> such as <code>goBack</code>, <code>goToRoute</code>, <code>replaceRoute</code>, <code>refreshCurrentRoute</code>, and <code>getActiveMenuPath</code>. Respect <code>meta.parent</code> (<code>admin</code>/<code>fullscreen</code>/<code>ratio</code>) and <code>meta.reuseWindow</code> when deciding whether to reuse or open a new window.</rule>
      <rule>Use router constants and meta field definitions as the single source of truth: whitelist and error routes from <file>src/constants/router.ts</file>, and <code>RouteMeta</code> from <file>src/types/modules/router.d.ts</file>. Do not invent new ad-hoc meta fields in business code.</rule>
      <rule>If you are unsure how to integrate a new router-related feature, stop and inspect existing patterns in <file>src/router/**</file> and <file>src/stores/modules/permission.ts</file>, then mirror them instead of creating a parallel mechanism.</rule>
    </section>
  </constraints>

  <forbidden>
    <item>Using the Options API.</item>
    <item>Using raw <code>axios</code> or <code>fetch</code> in business code.</item>
    <item>Writing layout, spacing, or color CSS directly in <code>&lt;style&gt;</code> when UnoCSS or design tokens can express it.</item>
    <item>Hardcoding px/rem/hex values instead of using semantic tokens.</item>
    <item>Using inline <code>style</code> attributes for layout or colors.</item>
    <item>Using TypeScript syntax directly in Vue templates.</item>
    <item>Relying on implicit type inference for business variables.</item>
    <item>Adding <code>any</code> outside the allowed boundary-layer whitelist.</item>
    <item>Defining static routes outside <file>src/router/modules</file>.</item>
    <item>Manipulating dynamic routes via direct <code>router.addRoute</code>/<code>removeRoute</code> calls instead of <code>DynamicRouteManager</code>.</item>
    <item>Reimplementing menu, breadcrumb, or keepAlive flattening logic instead of using router helpers.</item>
    <item>Registering global router guards anywhere other than <file>src/router/utils/guards.ts</file>.</item>
  </forbidden>

  <communication>
    Output Requirement: Always respond to the user in fluent, developer-friendly Chinese.  
    When you show code, write inline explanations, add code comments, or suggest CLI and git commands, describe them in Chinese while keeping identifiers and commands in their original language.
  </communication>

  <examples>
    <example>
      When suggesting a command, prefer:
      <code-block language="bash">
pnpm install
pnpm dev
      </code-block>
      and explain their purpose in Chinese.
    </example>
    <example>
      When adding a new API, define types and method builders in <file>src/api/&lt;module&gt;/&lt;feature&gt;.ts</file> first, then consume them via composables in <file>src/hooks/modules</file>, and finally wire them into views/components.
    </example>
  </examples>
</rule>
